# Definitions

## Javascript, HTML, & CSS, oh my!
  
· Javascript is the collection of lirbaries that provide the blueprints of building webpages and web applications. 
· HTML is the actual code to build out web based content.
· CSS aka cascading style sheets are the way the content is styled. 

## Core concepts

    The Grammar of Javascript
        Structure of code on the page
        Structure of each sentence
    Adding other elements like images, tables, lists, etc
 
    JavaScript programs: Called scripts or code that composed of statement that use variables, values, operators, expressions, and keywords to perform actions.

    Variables: Containers that store data values. Use a keyword like let for variables that can change and const for variables that remain constant.

    Example: 

    Using let (modern, value can be changed)
    let userName = "John";
    let userAge = 25;

    Using const (value cannot be changed after assignment)
    const pi = 3.14159;
    const siteName = "MDN Web Docs";

    Values: Stored in a variable. In the examples above, the values are "John", 25, 3.14159, and "MDN Web Docs"

    Data types: Numbers (intergers and floating point numbers), Strings "Hello, world!", Booleans (true/false---typically used for conditional logic), and objects (which store collections of data) 

    Functions: Reuable blocks of code that perform specific tasks. They're essential for structuring code & executing the same logic multiple times without having repeat the same code. 

    Control flow: The order in which statements are executed. If then/else statements are a good example of this.

    DOM (Document Object Model): Provides the ability to interact with the web page's structure. 


  
  
